# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# OPTIONAL — only needed if `typst` or `pdftoppm` aren't on your PATH.
#
# This file is NOT a configuration file in the usual sense. There are no
# secrets, API keys, or per-user credentials here — just binary path overrides.
#
# In the common case (Typst installed via `brew install typst`,
# `winget install Typst.Typst`, `cargo install typst-cli`, etc., and poppler
# installed via the package manager), both binaries are on PATH and you can
# ignore this file entirely. `scripts/build.sh` and `scripts/test.sh` only
# source `.env` if it exists; otherwise they fall back to `command -v`.
#
# Create a `.env` only when you have a specific reason:
#   • Windows + `winget install Typst.Typst` didn't add typst.exe to PATH
#     (the binary lands in a deep WinGet directory and `where typst` fails).
#   • You want to pin a specific Typst version different from your
#     package manager's default.
#   • You're running on a CI runner without PATH control.
#
# To use: `cp .env.example .env`, then uncomment and edit the lines you need.
# `.env` is gitignored — it never enters the public repository.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Path to the Typst binary. Default: `typst` looked up via $PATH.
# TYPST=/usr/local/bin/typst
# TYPST=/path/to/typst

# Path to pdftoppm (from poppler). Default: `pdftoppm` looked up via $PATH.
# Needed for `--preview` and `scripts/diff-preview.sh` only.
# PDFTOPPM=/usr/local/bin/pdftoppm
# PDFTOPPM=/path/to/pdftoppm
